occurrenceRemarks: Observed in the parking lot of the Shipyard and Titanic Rock formations near Tumbler Ridge, BC, Canada. No one had seen a fox all day. We'd finished our hike and were eating our lunches. I dropped a container of nuts which spilt out. I picked it up, turned and this vixen was creeping up to get the spilt food. Clearly habituated to people and used to being fed. It must have been waiting in hiding till the sound of a dropping container alerted it to come out and check.
